go-post-process: use Go module proxy for vendoring

Some Go modules (e.g. github.com/hexops/gotextdiff) can't be fetched
directly from GitHub because git prompts for credentials. The Go module
proxy at proxy.golang.org has cached copies.

--- a/support/download/go-post-process
+++ b/support/download/go-post-process
@@ -30,6 +30,7 @@
     exit 1
 fi
 
+export GOPROXY="${GOPROXY:-https://proxy.golang.org,direct}"
 go mod vendor -v -modcacherw
 popd > /dev/null
 
